  {
    "id": 2,
    "chunk_text": "[UNITED KINGDOM (UK)] Financial Guidelines: To obtain a student visa, students must prove they have enough funds to cover the first year's tuition fees plus living expenses. The official living expense requirement is \u00a31,334 per month for up to 9 months (\u00a312,006 total) inside London, and \u00a31,023 per month (\u00a39,207 total) outside London. Funds must be held in a bank account for a continuous period of at least 28 days before the visa application.",
